content:
Schedule a Recipe to Run Automatically

You can schedule a CRM Analytics recipe to run at a specific time or after an event. Use time-based scheduling to ensure that fresh data is available by a particular time or to run the job during non-business hours.

To schedule a recipe:

* In Data Manager, on the Recipes tab, click the triangle next to the recipe name and select Schedule.
* Select Time-based under Schedule Mode, then choose the time to run the recipe.
* If you have a CRM Analytics Plus license, you can set the schedule to run every 5, 15, 20, or 30 minutes.

To schedule the recipe to run after its related data sync:

* Select Event-based under Schedule Mode.
* Choose the events to trigger this schedule, such as The Salesforce local syncs or The selected CSVs are updated.
* You can select one or more events and make multiple selections of different types.

Required Editions and User Permissions

* Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
* Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.
* Also available in Developer Edition.

Needed permissions:

* Edit Dataset Recipes OR Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows
title: Scheduling Recipes in CRM Analytics
